{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980400673,"sessionID":"ses_1cc81798affeY6djrRh3to6wSK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ttn1ZaTGV9T8RFIyBsRn6QiP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json","offset":1,"limit":400},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"**Preferred term label:**\\nKidney Interpolar Region\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\nCentral Pole of Kidney\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nThis is already defined in NCIT: \\nKidney Interpolar Region\\nhttp://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C186124Copy\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\n\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n3:   \"comments\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87A-zih\",\n6:       \"author\": {\n7:         \"login\": \"taylordm\"\n8:       },\n9:       \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n10:       \"body\": \"Needed for dGTEx sampling of Kidney\",\n11:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-08-29T17:09:06Z\",\n12:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n13:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n14:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n15:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n16:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3237689505\",\n17:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n18:     },\n19:     {\n20:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87DlVwy\",\n21:       \"author\": {\n22:         \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n23:       },\n24:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n25:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please plan adding this term to Uberon. Look at the placement in NCIT, and find a good literature or textbook reference to use for the definition. Report findings on this issue before making a PR\",\n26:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T15:14:25Z\",\n27:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n28:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n29:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n30:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n31:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281345586\",\n32:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n33:     },\n34:     {\n35:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87DlivQ\",\n36:       \"author\": {\n37:         \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n38:       },\n39:       \"authorAssociation\": \"COLLABORATOR\",\n40:       \"body\": \"## Research Findings for Kidney Interpolar Region\\n\\n@dragon-ai-agent has completed the research for adding \\\"Kidney Interpolar Region\\\" to UBERON. Here are the comprehensive findings:\\n\\n### Anatomical Definition\\nThe **kidney interpolar region** (synonym: \\\"central pole of kidney\\\") is the middle portion of the kidney located between the upper and lower poles. It represents approximately the middle third of the kidney's longitudinal axis and is bounded by:\\n- Superior boundary: Upper pole of kidney\\n- Inferior boundary: Lower pole of kidney  \\n- Contains central portions of both renal cortex and medulla\\n\\n### NCIT Analysis\\n- NCIT term: C186124 \\\"Kidney Interpolar Region\\\"\\n- Already defined in NCIT with appropriate placement\\n- Used extensively in clinical radiology and pathology\\n\\n### Literature Support\\nFound strong literature support with multiple authoritative references:\\n- **Key PMIDs for definition**: PMID:25659322, PMID:28444432, PMID:15876515, PMID:32156458, PMID:27834214\\n- Widely used in medical imaging, surgical planning, and nephrology literature\\n- Established anatomical concept in human anatomy textbooks and clinical practice\\n\\n### Proposed UBERON Placement\\nBased on analysis of existing kidney anatomy terms in UBERON:\\n\\n**Parent class**: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part\\n- **Relationships**: \\n  - part_of UBERON:0002113 ! kidney\\n  - contributes_to_morphology_of UBERON:0002113 ! kidney\\n\\n**Logical definition pattern** (following existing kidney part patterns):\\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part  \\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002113 ! kidney\\n\\n### Current UBERON Status\\n- ✅ No conflicting terms found\\n- ✅ Fits well with existing kidney anatomy hierarchy\\n- ✅ Upper/lower pole terms don't currently exist (could be added later if needed)\\n- ✅ Clear relationships to existing terms like cortex of kidney, renal medulla\\n\\n### Recommendation\\n**Ready to proceed** with term creation. The research shows:\\n1. Strong anatomical... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n41:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T15:23:21Z\",\n42:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n43:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n44:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n45:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n46:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281398736\",\n47:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n48:     },\n49:     {\n50:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87Dl24c\",\n51:       \"author\": {\n52:         \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n53:       },\n54:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n55:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please do it, with these modifications\\n\\n- don't include a logical definition. This is only for N+S conditions\\n- don't bother with the contributes_to_morphology_of. You are right that we have done this in the past, but let's keep it simple\\n- don't use any of these PMIDs\\n\\nCredit @taylordm her ORCID is https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3302-4610\",\n56:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T15:37:16Z\",\n57:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n58:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n59:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n60:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n61:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281481244\",\n62:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n63:     },\n64:     {\n65:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87Dl_VK\",\n66:       \"author\": {\n67:         \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n68:       },\n69:       \"authorAssociation\": \"COLLABORATOR\",\n70:       \"body\": \"## Implementation Progress\\n\\n@dragon-ai-agent has prepared the kidney interpolar region term with the requested modifications:\\n\\n### Term Details Created\\n- ID: UBERON:7770009 (next available in sequence)\\n- Name: kidney interpolar region\\n- Synonyms: \\n  - central pole of kidney (EXACT)\\n  - interpolar region of kidney (EXACT)\\n- Definition: The middle portion of the kidney situated between the upper pole and the lower pole, representing approximately the middle third of the kidney along its longitudinal axis. [Wikipedia:Kidney]\\n\\n### Applied Modifications per @cmungall\\n✅ No logical definition - Removed intersection_of axioms (only for N+S conditions)\\n✅ No contributes_to_morphology_of - Simplified relationships  \\n✅ No PMIDs - Using only Wikipedia reference as requested  \\n✅ Credited @taylordm - Added dc-contributor with ORCID 0000-0002-3302-4610  \\n\\n### Simplified Structure\\nis_a: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part\\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002113 ! kidney\\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3302-4610 ! Danielle Taylor\\n\\n### Next Steps\\nCurrently awaiting file edit permissions to add the term to src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo. Once permissions are granted, I will:\\n1. Insert the complete term definition\\n2. Commit the changes \\n3. Create a PR for review\\n\\nThe term is ready and follows all UBERON formatting standards and the specific requirements outlined.\\n\\n@dragon-ai-agent\",\n71:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T15:44:00Z\",\n72:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n73:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n74:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n75:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n76:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281515850\",\n77:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n78:     },\n79:     {\n80:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87DnxOP\",\n81:       \"author\": {\n82:         \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n83:       },\n84:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n85:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please try again. My apologies, your permissions were not set correctly before. It should work now.\\n\\nAnd it's Deanne not Danielle\",\n86:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-09-11T17:23:09Z\",\n87:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n88:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n89:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n90:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n91:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3281982351\",\n92:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n93:     }\n94:   ],\n95:   \"title\": \"dGTEx terms needed in Uberon\",\n96:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604\"\n97: }\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"**Preferred term label:**\\nKidney Interpolar Region\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\nCentral Pole of Kidney\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nThis is already defined in NCIT: \\nKidney Interpolar Region\\nhttp://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C186124Copy\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\n\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87A-zih\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"taylordm\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n      \"body\": \"Needed for dGTEx sampling of Kidney\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-08-29T17:09:06Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3604#issuecomment-3237689505\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87DlVwy\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778980400607,"end":1778980400670}},"id":"prt_e337eadd6001pyXC5aRLzMLbDd","sessionID":"ses_1cc81798affeY6djrRh3to6wSK","messageID":"msg_e337e9f86001zVU76FKJpX5bTO"}}
